description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Medical Director for System Improvement will work with the Regional Medical Director to support the delivery of NHS England &amp; Improvement’s objectives across the region and help improve the quality of clinical services across primary, community and secondary care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post-holder will provide professional leadership to the regional and local clinical networks, ensuring that the commissioning of services, is consistent with safe, high quality care and good patient experience. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an exceptional candidate who is a medical practitioner with current GMC registration and a highly experienced clinician with the credibility and leadership skills to command the respect of all clinical and non-clinical professional colleagues.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful candidate will have senior leadership experience in the NHS and have operated at or close to Board level within a Trust or CCG.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A good understanding of primary care and an appreciation of primary care contracting processes will would also be desirable.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note: these opportunities are open to secondees on secondment into NHSE &amp; I from an external organisation. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: sharron.hogan1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Head of Clinical Delivery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Sharron.Hogan1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07730374799&lt;/p&gt;
